From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 01:12:57 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: add test for atomic isolation in compact templates

Combines per-instantiation reorder with atomic false-sharing isolation: a compact class template with an atomic field isolates that field onto its own cache line in every instantiation (Box<long> and Box<int> both place counter at offset 0, n at 64). Validated against layout dumps.



diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-atomic-isolation-template.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-atomic-isolation-template.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..16a1a37bd
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-atomic-isolation-template.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@
+// HARD interaction: atomic false-sharing isolation inside a compact CLASS
+// TEMPLATE. The per-instantiation Sema::ActOnFields hook runs applyCompactLayout,
+// which both permutes the fields by alignment AND stamps the cache-line
+// AlignedAttr on the atomic. So every instantiation places its _Atomic counter
+// alone on cache line 0, with n pushed to line 64 -- combining the template
+// reorder (per-instantiation) with the atomic isolation.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+template <class T> compact struct Box {
+  char tag;
+  _Atomic T counter;
+  int n;
+};
+
+Box<long> bl;
+Box<int> bi;
+
+static_assert(sizeof(Box<long>) == 128, "atomic isolated in the instantiation");
+static_assert(sizeof(Box<int>) == 128, "atomic isolated in the instantiation");
+static_assert(alignof(Box<long>) == 64, "record alignment raised to the line");
+
+// CHECK:      struct Box<long>
+// CHECK:      0 |{{.*}}counter
+// CHECK:      64 |{{.*}}int n
+// CHECK:      struct Box<int>
+// CHECK:      0 |{{.*}}counter
+// CHECK:      64 |{{.*}}int n
